In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 1, 2012, as Loyalty Day in the United States. He reflects on the country's proud heritage and the journey towards prosperity for all. He emphasizes the commitment Americans have made to each other and the fundamental principles that unite the nation. The President acknowledges the challenges the country has overcome, such as civil war and segregation, and the spirit of service that has propelled progress. He recognizes the dedication of those who defend the country and contribute to their communities through volunteerism and civic participation. The President calls upon all Americans to reaffirm their allegiance to the United States, its Constitution, and its founding values.